  {
    "file": "internal/terraform/context_apply.go",
    "line": 276,
    "severity": "medium",
    "description": "In checkApplyTimeVariables, the second loop detects variables that were provided at apply time but were NOT set during the plan phase. For an ephemeral variable in this situation, the error is appended with the summary 'No value for required variable' — which is the exact same summary used in the first loop when a NEEDED variable is MISSING. The two situations are opposites: the first loop handles missing required variables; the second loop handles unexpected extra variables. Using 'No value for required variable' when the variable is unexpectedly present produces a confusing, misleading error message. The non-ephemeral branch of the same code correctly uses 'Unexpected new value for variable'.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/internal/terraform/context_apply.go
+++ b/internal/terraform/context_apply.go
@@ -273,7 +273,7 @@ func checkApplyTimeVariables(needed collections.Set[string], gotValues InputVal
